{"id":"11346","name":"Pleco","tagline":"Looks up the selected text in Pleco.","icon":"ios14 c946986751 g61564","latest":"33373","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut takes text from the share sheet and looks it up in the Pleco app. It works with English, Hanzi, and pinyin. </p>\n<p>Similar shortcuts import the text into the Pleco document reader, but what you usually want is for the word or phrase to be looked up in the dictionary. That’s what this shortcut does. Only longer text will be imported into the document reader.</p>\n<p><strong>To download:</strong> Tap the “Get Shortcut” button to the left. The Shortcuts app will open and offer to import the shortcut (if nothing happens after Shortcuts opens, come back and tap “Get Shortcut” again).</p>\n<p><strong>To use:</strong> Select text in iOS. Choose “Share…” item in the edit menu that pops up, select “Pleco,” and the selected text will be looked up in Pleco.</p>\n<p>If you run into any problems, please leave feedback below (requires login) or on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=@calion%20Re%20Pleco%3A\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>2.1.2 - June 1, 2022, 3:18 p.m.</strong></p><p>Updates to the readme</p>"}